Afrobeats queen Tiwa Savage has put across a surprise video call to the World 100m hurdles record holder, Tobi Amusan during which she gushed over her. Savage joined multitude over the world to congratulate the 25-year-old, who ran a time of 12.12 seconds, shaving almost a tenth of a second off the previous world record in the semi-finals of the World Championships in Oregon on before going on to win gold in the final on Sunday. The 42-year-old songstress noted she was about picking up her phone to make a celebratory post for Nigeria’s first-ever gold winner at the World Athletics Championships before she got a message from Papa Omisore. According to her, Papa informed her that Amusan has been trying to get in touch with her so she decided to do a Face time involving all three of them.   BBNaija: What will happen if Chichi and I align – Hermes     #BBNaija: Sheggz justifies peeping at Chichi during bath     #BBNaija S7: I’m sexual attracted to Chichi –…   Tiwa, praying for Amusan, thanked her for making Nigerians especially the women proud with her huge win while pledging one hundred percent for the athlete. Mummy Jam Jam said: “Thank you, thank you. God bless you. Any support, anything, I’m with you a 100%. I’m so happy for you,” Tiwa said as she gushed over Tobi. “I was about to post you. I picked up my phone and I got a message from Papa that you are trying to reach me. I was like, Wow!! I can’t wait to see you!” Captioning the video, she wrote: “I was literally about to post you and got this message. @ihurdle-33.0 you made every Nigerian especially women so proud and inspired today. God bless you Queen.”